<inglise> Council Directive 72/306/EEC of 2 August 1972 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the measures to be taken against the emission of pollutants from diesel engines for use in vehicles </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 72/306/EM&Uuml; s&otilde;idukite diiselmootorite heitmete vastu v&otilde;etavaid meetmeid k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta 2. august 1972 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 100 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the Economic and Social Committee; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the technical requirements which motor vehicles must satisfy pursuant to national laws relate, inter alia, to the emission of pollutants from diesel engines for use in vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: tehnilised n&otilde;uded, millele mootors&otilde;idukid peavad siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt vastama, k&auml;sitlevad muu hulgas s&otilde;idukite diiselmootorite heitmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas those requirements differ from one Member State to another; whereas it is therefore necessary that all the Member States adopt the same requirements either in addition to or in place of their existing rules, in order, in particular, to allow the EEC type approval procedure which was the subject of the Council Directive 1 of 6 February 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers to be applied in respect of each type of vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused n&otilde;uded on liikmesriigiti erinevad; seet&otilde;ttu on vajalik, et k&otilde;ik liikmesriigid kohaldaksid samu n&otilde;udeid, tehes olemasolevatesse eeskirjadesse lisandusi v&otilde;i asendades need uutega selleks, et eelk&otilde;ige oleks v&otilde;imalik rakendada iga s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi puhul EM&Uuml; t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusmenetlust, mida k&auml;sitletakse n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivis mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta; (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, it is desirable to follow the technical requirements adopted by the UN Economic Commission for Europe in its Regulation No 24 (Uniform provisions concerning the approval of vehicles equipped with diesel engines with regard to the emission of pollutants by the engine), which is annexed to the Agreement of 20 March 1958 concerning the adoption of uniform conditions of approval and reciprocal recognition of approval for motor vehicle equipment and parts 2; </inglise>
<eesti> on soovitatav arvesse v&otilde;tta tehnilisi n&otilde;udeid, mis on vastu v&otilde;etud &Uuml;RO Euroopa Majanduskomisjoni eeskirjas nr 24 (Diiselmootoriga s&otilde;idukite t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse &uuml;htsed s&auml;tted seoses diiselmootorite heitmetega), mis on lisatud 20. m&auml;rtsi 1958. aasta kokkuleppele mootors&otilde;idukite varustuse ja osade kinnitamise &uuml;htsete n&otilde;uete vastuv&otilde;tmise ja kinnitamise vastastikuse tunnustamise kohta, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive, "vehicle" means any vehicle with a diesel engine, intended for use on the road, with or without bodywork, having at least four wheels and a maximum design speed exceeding 25 km/h, with the exception of vehicles which run on rails, agricultural tractors and machines and public works vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis t&auml;hendab "s&otilde;iduk" teedel kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud, kerega v&otilde;i kereta, v&auml;hemalt neljarattalist mootors&otilde;idukit, mille valmistajakiirus &uuml;letab 25 km/h, v&auml;lja arvatud r&ouml;&ouml;bastel liikuvad s&otilde;idukid, p&otilde;llut&ouml;&ouml;traktorid ja -masinad ning muud liikurmasinad. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> No Member State may refuse to grant a vehicle EEC type approval or national type approval on the ground that pollutants are emitted by the diesel engine which drives the vehicle, if the engine complies with Annexes I, II, III, IV and VI. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski liikmesriik ei tohi keelduda s&otilde;idukile EM&Uuml; v&otilde;i siseriikliku t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse andmisest s&otilde;iduki diiselmootori heitmetega seotud p&otilde;hjustel, kui mootor vastab I, II, III, IV ja VI lisas etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member State which has granted type approval shall take the necessary measures to ensure that it is informed of any modification of a part or characteristic referred to in item 2.2 of Annex I. The competent authorities of that Member State shall decide whether fresh tests should be carried out on the modified vehicle and a fresh report drawn up. </inglise>
<eesti> T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse andnud liikmesriik v&otilde;tab vajalikud meetmed, et tagada informeeritus k&otilde;ikidest I lisa punktis 2.2 nimetatud osades v&otilde;i karakteristikutes tehtud muudatustest. K&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused otsustavad muudatustega s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi uuesti katsetamise ning uue katseprotokolli koostamise vajaduse &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the tests reveal failure to comply with this Directive, the modification shall not be approved. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui katsete tulemusena ilmnevad k&otilde;rvalekaldumised k&auml;esoleva direktiivi n&otilde;uetest, siis muudatust ei kinnitata. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The amendments necessary for adjusting the Annexes so as to take account of technical progress shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of the Council Directive of 6 February 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers. </inglise>
<eesti> Muudatused, mis on vajalikud lisades esitatud n&otilde;uete kohandamiseks tehnika arenguga, v&otilde;etakse vastu mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivi artiklis 13 etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall put into force the provisions needed in order to comply with this Directive within eighteen months of its notification and shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi t&auml;itmiseks vajalikud s&auml;tted 18 kuu jooksul alates direktiivi teatavakstegemisest ning teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Furthermore, once notification of this directive has been effected the Member States shall ensure that the Commission is informed, in time for it to submit its comments, of the most important laws, regulations and administrative provisions which they envisage adopting in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Niipea kui k&auml;esolev direktiiv on teatavaks tehtud, tagavad liikmesriigid komisjoni piisavalt aegsa informeerimise k&otilde;igist &otilde;igusnormide eeln&otilde;udest, mis liikmesriigid kavatsevad k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastu v&otilde;tta, et komisjon saaks esitada oma m&auml;rkused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 2 August 1972 For the Council </inglise>
